Here's a short JavaScript function that calculates the factorial of a given number:

```javascript
/**
 * Calculates the factorial of a given number.
 * @param {number} n - The number to calculate the factorial for.
 * @returns {number} The factorial of the input number.
 */
function factorial(n) {
    if (n === 0 || n === 1) return 1;
    return n * factorial(n - 1);
}
```

This function uses recursion to calculate the factorial. It returns 1 for inputs of 0 or 1, and otherwise multiplies the input by the factorial of the input minus one.
